tion": "Follicle-stimulating hormone", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9982126355171204, "span": {"begin": 1248, "end": 1276}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6046"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "FSH", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9976440668106079, "span": {"begin": 1278, "end": 1281}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5351"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "Luteinizing hormone", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9986456036567688, "span": {"begin": 1287, "end": 1306}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:5351"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "LH", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9984694123268127, "span": {"begin": 1308, "end": 1310}}], "text": "Gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) is produced by the hypothalamus. &nbsp;Gonadotropin-releasing hormone is a peptide hormone composed of 10 amino acids (Hassanein et al. 2024). &nbsp;Increases in GnRH stimulate increased production of Luteinizing hormone (LH) and Follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), two types of gonadotropins. GnRH activation of gonadotropin production is triggered via a G-protein, phospholipase C activation, and mitogen-activated protein kinase (MAPK) pathway activation (Hassanein et al. 2024). &nbsp;LH and FSH are important hormones in the hypothalamus- pituitary-gonadal (HPG) axis. &nbsp;Increased GnRH release leads to increased production of gonadotropins in the anterior pituitary gland. &nbsp;   Gonadotropins are hormones in mammals that cue development of reproductive organs to maturity (Casarini and Simoni 2021; Howard 2021) and the different phases of the estrus cycle (Uenoyama et al. 2021). &nbsp;Gonadotropins are composed of two subunits: a 90-100 amino acid alpha subunit that is identical for all gonadotropins for a species, and a 105-150 amino acid beta subunit that are unique to each gonadotropin but exhibit large similarities in order to interact with alpha subunits (Cahoreau et al 2015). &nbsp;Follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) and Luteinizing hormone (LH) are released from the anterior pituitary gland (Howard 2021). &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:21:01 +0000 2026"}